lead_paragraph: Brendan Hansen, the world-record holder in the 200-meter breaststroke, won the event in 2 minutes 9.91 seconds at the United States Championships in Indianapolis. Michael Phelps, who rarely enters the 200 meters, was 11th. Other winners were Kathleen Hersey and Darvis Tarwater in the 200 butterfly, Rebecca Soni in the 200 breaststroke, Kate Ziegler in the 800 freestyle and Erik Vendt in the 1,500 freestyle.
